The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal says it will discipline supporters of embattled eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede. DURBAN - The eThekwini Metro is counting the cost of damage that supporters of Mayor Zandile Gumede have caused. The City Hall and city centre were brought to a standstill by protest action. While Gumede’s supporters have taken her political fight to the streets of Durban, city officials are counting the financial cost of the city's shutdown. WATCH: ANC to take action against Gumede marchers The City Hall continues to be under siege and has been brought to a grinding halt by the mayor’s supporters. Officials say Thursday’s chaos and disruptions affected the city’s service delivery and revenue collection services. Meanwhile, the ANC in KwaZulu-Natal says it will discipline Gumede's supporters. EXCLUSIVE: eThekwini mayor breaks her silence Protesters want Gumede to return to work immediately. Gumede says she’s in limbo as she awaits the ANC's decision.